## Description {#details}

Data structure to hold cached (LLVM-IR) information.

All attributes are given an <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/informationcache">InformationCache</a> object at creation time to avoid inspection of the IR by all of them individually. This default <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/informationcache">InformationCache</a> will hold information required by &#39;default&#39; attributes, thus the ones deduced when <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/attributor/#adab9b2e1a33cfbe6f0fa6443046dcaf8">Attributor::identifyDefaultAbstractAttributes</a>(..) is called.

If custom abstract attributes, registered manually through Attributor::registerAA(...), need more information, especially if it is not reusable, it is advised to inherit from the <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/informationcache">InformationCache</a> and cast the instance down in the abstract attributes.

Definition at line 1203 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h">Attributor.h</a>.
